originalText.text:
Dr. Josh and his team are trying to scare people into spending thousands of dollars just to have some pressure placed on their backs! At my first appointment, Dr. Josh did his initial examination and then wouldn’t adjust me, even though I was in extreme pain and was having trouble breathing (I’ve been to a few chiropractors before and none of them would let me leave their office in the condition I was in). I still had to pay my $55 copay and arrange another appointment. At my second appointment, Dr. Josh tried to tell me my back was so bad that I needed to be on a $5600 3-month treatment plan! I couldn’t afford that so he said he GUESSED he could adjust me and I would just pay the copay again but that I should really think about it and come back in the next week. I wanted a second opinion so I asked to have my X-rays sent to me (which cost another $35 for reasons they couldn’t articulate) and I sent them to my chiropractor back home. She said she could have me fixed in 1-2 sessions!
DO NOT GO HERE! THEY WILL RIP YOU OFF!!
